issues.description: The template repository’s Lecture class declares the existing attributes lectureName and numberOfInscribedStudents as public, but the UML in the problem statement uses “-” (private) and the solution defines all attributes as private, resulting in a visibility mismatch that may confuse students about encapsulation and where to add or modify fields.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the visibility of the existing fields lectureName and numberOfInscribedStudents in the template to private, matching the UML and solution, so students consistently work with private attributes and implement getters/setters.
